  &lt;p id="31Wchq"&gt;In a bold bid to turn digital crooks away from a life of crime, Microsoft is offering a 50 percent discount on its Office suite to some people using pirated versions. &lt;a href="https://www.ghacks.net/2021/12/03/pirated-versions-of-office-are-getting-a-discount-offer-for-a-microsoft-365-subscription/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ghacks &lt;/em&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; that a new message in the Office ribbon bar is appearing on pirated Office apps, tempting people with a 50 percent discount on a genuine Microsoft 365 subscription.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kHxaWg"&gt;The message links to an &lt;a href="https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD%2FrLJHOac&amp;amp;mid=24542&amp;amp;u1=verge&amp;amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.microsoft.com%2Fen-US%2Fmicrosoft-365%2Fbuy%2Fget-genuine-b%3Focid%3Dprod_unlicensed_cons_fuel_acq_getgenuine50_buy%26rtc%3D1" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;official Microsoft website&lt;/a&gt; that claims “pirated software exposes your PC to security threats.” Microsoft warns Office pirates that they run the risk of running into viruses, malware, data loss, identify theft, and the inability to receive critical updates.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;Image: Ghacks&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;The 50 percent discount notification.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p id="m33Z85"&gt;The discount brings the price of a...&lt;/p&gt;
